WEBVTT

03:08.938 --> 03:11.106
WILLIE:
Memory is a funny thing.

03:11.900 --> 03:16.403
Recollections slip in and out
and around in time...

03:17.071 --> 03:20.115
...leaving plenty of room
to weave and backtrack...

03:20.325 --> 03:22.618
...and drift and glide.

03:23.620 --> 03:25.787
In my life, I've found that...

03:25.955 --> 03:28.624
...memories of the spirit
linger and sweeten...

03:28.833 --> 03:32.127
...long after memories
of the brain have faded.

03:32.462 --> 03:36.131
My fondest memories are
of my childhood days...

03:36.341 --> 03:38.842
...back in Yazoo, Mississippi.

03:39.302 --> 03:41.345
I can still see the town now.

03:41.596 --> 03:44.473
Ten thousand souls, and nothing doing.

03:44.766 --> 03:48.852
Where the old men sat drowsily
in straw-bottom chairs...

03:49.103 --> 03:52.564
...watching the big cars
with out-of-state plates whip by.

03:52.815 --> 03:54.483
Drivers hardly knowing...

03:54.651 --> 03:58.153
...and certainly not caring
what place this was.

03:58.363 --> 04:00.656
There was a war going on then.

04:00.865 --> 04:02.866
And it touched our lives every day.

04:03.660 --> 04:06.286
War, President Roosevelt
reminded us...

04:06.496 --> 04:10.707
...required everybody to make
sacrifices. And boy, we did.

04:12.669 --> 04:16.004
The cotton grew tall that year,
the summer of 1 942...

04:16.839 --> 04:18.798
...but I sure didn't.

04:19.384 --> 04:21.677
Matter of fact,
I stayed so small and puny...

04:21.886 --> 04:24.346
...I was a target
for the neighborhood bullies.

04:25.181 --> 04:27.849
Fortunately, I lived next door
to Dink Jenkins...

04:28.017 --> 04:31.186
...Yazoo's best athlete
and favorite son.

04:31.854 --> 04:34.523
-Dink?
-Yeah?

04:34.816 --> 04:36.650
Where do you think they'll send you?

04:37.527 --> 04:41.321
Probably Fort Benning for basic,
then overseas, l reckon.

04:42.115 --> 04:43.865
How long will you be gone?

04:44.492 --> 04:46.535
That's hard to say.

04:48.538 --> 04:53.000
If you're not home, who will
show me how to throw a curve ball?

04:53.209 --> 04:55.043
You promised to show me.

04:55.253 --> 04:57.838
Partner, you're gonna do just fine.

04:58.047 --> 05:00.924
While I'm gone, you'll make
friends your own age...

05:01.175 --> 05:05.554
...and who knows,
you might even meet a girl.

05:06.764 --> 05:07.806
JACK:
Will!

05:08.141 --> 05:09.558
Suppertime!

05:10.268 --> 05:13.353
WlLLIE:
This was a time of large families.

05:13.563 --> 05:16.565
Four or five kids, sometimes more.

05:17.233 --> 05:20.444
So needless to say,
ours was already unusual...

05:20.737 --> 05:23.238
...what with me being the only child.

05:23.573 --> 05:26.783
My mother was lively and talkative.

05:27.035 --> 05:29.661
Certainly didn't fit
the housewife mold.

05:30.246 --> 05:31.788
And my daddy....

05:33.082 --> 05:35.751
Well, my daddy was
stern and overbearing.

05:36.419 --> 05:40.380
He was a war veteran
and had lost his leg in battle.

05:40.798 --> 05:43.967
And from most accounts,
it changed him.

05:44.260 --> 05:48.597
Sometimes it seemed that
along with that leg...

05:48.931 --> 05:51.725
...he'd also lost
a piece of his heart.

05:58.691 --> 06:01.276
[MUSlC PLAYS OVER RADlO]

06:03.071 --> 06:04.237
ELLEN:
Okay?

06:04.447 --> 06:07.324
You know I.C.? Colored fellow
at the service station?

06:07.617 --> 06:08.617
ELLEN:
Sure.

06:10.286 --> 06:12.913
-His son came back from Europe today.
ELLEN: Wonderful.

06:13.122 --> 06:14.456
In a box.

06:17.960 --> 06:21.296
Somebody around here's gonna
be having a birthday pretty soon.

06:21.506 --> 06:24.424
You been thinking about
how you want to celebrate?

06:24.634 --> 06:27.135
A party maybe? Hmm?

06:30.223 --> 06:32.808
Will, your mother
asked you a question.

06:32.975 --> 06:36.144
Stop. You're lucky to have that food,
with the rationing.

06:36.813 --> 06:39.314
Would you like a party
or wouldn't you?

06:39.607 --> 06:40.774
I guess.

06:42.151 --> 06:45.487
I picked these up today
at Carr's drugstore.

06:47.490 --> 06:49.032
Invitations?

06:50.034 --> 06:53.662
You can't very well have a party
without guests, now can you?

06:55.540 --> 06:59.668
After supper, you fill them out and
give them to your friends tomorrow.

07:00.503 --> 07:01.837
Like who?

07:02.839 --> 07:03.880
JACK:
Well....

07:04.173 --> 07:05.674
What about John Abner?

07:06.843 --> 07:09.970
He's 5. He still wets his pants.

07:10.680 --> 07:14.641
There are plenty of children
who would love to attend your party.

07:14.851 --> 07:18.019
Your mother went to a lot
of trouble to get invitations.

07:18.187 --> 07:20.188
And you will fill them out.

07:24.652 --> 07:26.528
Can l be excused?

07:27.071 --> 07:28.321
Yes, you may.

07:30.533 --> 07:32.492
Don't forget your invitations.

07:47.216 --> 07:48.550
[SIGHS]

07:48.718 --> 07:50.385
What are we gonna do?

07:50.928 --> 07:53.847
He's gonna be so lonely without Dink.

07:55.433 --> 07:58.560
Maybe we should reconsider
what we talked about before.

07:58.728 --> 08:01.396
Absolutely not.
We've been over this already.

08:01.564 --> 08:04.733
It is not a good idea.
Not for Will, not now.

08:04.901 --> 08:07.068
He is still too young.

08:09.113 --> 08:10.197
Hmm.

08:14.911 --> 08:16.870
[WHOOPlNG AND HOLLERlNG]

08:17.079 --> 08:18.747
[CAR HONKING]

08:18.956 --> 08:21.458
GIRL: Y'all be careful.
-All right, we will!

08:22.752 --> 08:24.461
SOLDlER:
Hey, you wait for us!

08:29.258 --> 08:30.383
MR. JENKlNS:
Smile.

08:33.554 --> 08:35.263
MRS. JENKlNS:
You take care, you hear?

08:36.349 --> 08:37.390
SOLDlER:
Come on, Jenkins!

08:37.600 --> 08:39.768
Can't keep old Adolf a-waitin'!

08:40.602 --> 08:41.895
All right.

08:47.360 --> 08:48.902
DINK:
Fellas, y'all want to come?

08:50.363 --> 08:52.113
BlG BOY:
We was wondering....

08:53.741 --> 08:55.617
We wanted you to sign our football.

08:55.785 --> 08:57.869
You know, as a souvenir.

08:58.079 --> 08:59.120
DINK:
All right.

08:59.288 --> 09:01.456
Beside Slingin' Sammy Baugh.

09:02.291 --> 09:04.459
His name came with the ball.

09:04.794 --> 09:07.128
This might be a little soon,
don't you think?

09:07.296 --> 09:09.965
I ain't even played college ball yet.

09:10.132 --> 09:11.967
Jenkins, come on. Let's go!

09:14.262 --> 09:16.638
HENJlE: Thanks, Dink.
BlG BOY: Let me see!

09:16.973 --> 09:19.474
Willie-boy, aren't you
gonna wish me luck?

09:20.810 --> 09:23.395
-Y'all give me a second, okay?
SOLDlER: Come on.

09:26.315 --> 09:27.649
DINK:
What's the matter?

09:27.817 --> 09:28.858
Huh?

09:29.026 --> 09:33.446
Hey, when l get back, I'll show you
how to throw that curve ball.

09:34.156 --> 09:35.198
Really?

09:35.366 --> 09:38.326
Shoot, yeah, really.
Don't forget to write me.

09:38.494 --> 09:41.037
Give the letters to my mama.
She'll send them.

09:41.831 --> 09:45.333
I want you to tell me everything
that happens around here, okay?

09:45.543 --> 09:47.335
Don't leave nothing out.

09:47.837 --> 09:49.004
All right?

09:49.297 --> 09:50.839
This is mine.

09:51.299 --> 09:53.174
I hope it'll mean something to you.

09:54.010 --> 09:55.051
Oh!

09:55.344 --> 09:57.971
You didn't think l'd forget
your birthday, did you?

09:58.180 --> 10:00.682
-Thanks, Dink.
-All right.

10:01.517 --> 10:02.934
I'll see you.

10:03.894 --> 10:04.936
See you!

10:06.147 --> 10:07.480
Good luck!

10:11.193 --> 10:12.819
SOLDlER:
Here we go now!

10:14.989 --> 10:16.031
Bye-bye, ladies!

10:16.198 --> 10:19.034
GIRLS:
Bye! Bye, Dink!

10:19.243 --> 10:22.203
KlDS:
Bye! Good luck!

10:47.980 --> 10:50.231
BlG BOY:
Twenty-four, 32, hut, hut!

10:51.275 --> 10:53.735
SPlT:
Pass it. Here, I'm open!

10:55.029 --> 10:56.780
[KIDS LAUGH]

10:58.866 --> 11:01.076
JACK:
Will. Hon.

11:01.243 --> 11:02.285
SPlT:
Hon?!

11:03.412 --> 11:05.246
BlG BOY:
Goofball can't even catch!

11:06.374 --> 11:07.916
Time to come in.

11:08.751 --> 11:11.795
Why didn't you catch it,
you big titty-baby?

11:12.755 --> 11:14.089
Let me see it.

11:15.424 --> 11:19.636
I can't believe that titty-baby lives
right next door to Dink Jenkins.

11:20.137 --> 11:21.721
What a waste!

11:25.434 --> 11:27.769
GRANDMA:
Here, let me help you.

11:37.029 --> 11:41.408
They say this is what all the dapper
young men in Memphis are wearing.

11:41.951 --> 11:43.660
WlLLIE:
Thank you, Grandma.

11:50.334 --> 11:52.961
Huck Finn! Thank you, Grandpa!

11:53.129 --> 11:54.796
There's cussing in it.

12:01.137 --> 12:02.137
There.

12:05.850 --> 12:08.059
A pocketknife!

12:08.978 --> 12:10.311
AUNT MAGGlE:
Relax, worry-boy.

12:10.479 --> 12:12.313
It's just fingernail clippers.

12:16.819 --> 12:18.987
It does have a blade, though.

12:19.864 --> 12:21.656
WlLLIE:
Thank you, Aunt Maggie.

12:22.783 --> 12:23.825
JACK:
Will.

12:25.161 --> 12:26.828
This one's from me.

12:27.621 --> 12:29.622
It was mine when I was a boy.

12:42.845 --> 12:45.472
Thank you, Daddy. lt's nice.

12:53.689 --> 12:54.689
JACK:
Will.

12:55.232 --> 12:57.358
Say thank you for your nice presents.

12:57.526 --> 12:58.568
Wait.

12:58.736 --> 13:00.612
There's one more.

13:10.247 --> 13:11.372
I thought we agreed.

13:11.707 --> 13:13.041
You agreed.

13:13.876 --> 13:15.543
This is from Daddy and me.

13:15.836 --> 13:17.378
I hope you like it.

13:18.047 --> 13:21.216
[PUPPY WHlNlNG]

13:21.509 --> 13:23.009
You mean he's mine?!

13:23.219 --> 13:24.761
He's all yours.

13:26.347 --> 13:27.388
I hope you like it.

13:32.144 --> 13:33.394
Oh.

13:41.862 --> 13:42.904
I'm sorry.

13:44.031 --> 13:45.532
Jack, be sensible.

13:47.660 --> 13:49.536
Your mother made a mistake.

13:50.246 --> 13:52.914
-We can't keep a dog. Not now.
-What?

13:55.918 --> 13:56.960
Maybe next year.

13:58.587 --> 13:59.879
But why?

14:01.799 --> 14:03.758
I know you're disappointed...

14:03.968 --> 14:06.386
...but l want you to know that...

14:06.595 --> 14:08.972
...l'm gonna find
a real good home for him.

14:24.780 --> 14:25.989
[KNOCKlNG ON DOOR]

14:35.416 --> 14:37.625
I know you're upset with us.

14:38.210 --> 14:40.628
I'm so sorry about what happened.

14:41.255 --> 14:44.465
Did you ever get your birthday present
taken away from you?

14:47.511 --> 14:48.720
[SIGHS]

14:50.139 --> 14:53.600
Your father just doesn't think
you're quite ready for a dog yet.

14:53.976 --> 14:57.312
I am ready to have a dog. I'm 9.

14:58.480 --> 15:00.815
Lots of kids younger
than me have dogs.

15:01.150 --> 15:04.277
Ralph Atkinson. He's only 3.

15:05.154 --> 15:07.864
He has two dogs, a cat and bird.

15:08.532 --> 15:10.658
He can stick his head
in the dog's mouth.

15:11.452 --> 15:13.661
Hmm. That's impressive.

15:14.288 --> 15:16.623
I can take care of a dog, Mom.

15:17.541 --> 15:20.001
Really, l can.

15:24.965 --> 15:26.257
Will.

15:28.177 --> 15:30.678
You just be a big boy
about this, okay?

15:49.531 --> 15:51.699
[PUPPY WHlNES]

15:59.291 --> 16:00.667
He'll be fine.

16:02.544 --> 16:04.170
I don't think so.

16:04.380 --> 16:05.713
You know...

16:06.215 --> 16:08.841
...if anybody here
deserves to be angry, it's me.

16:09.051 --> 16:10.593
You went behind my back.

16:12.429 --> 16:17.058
You didn't give me any choice.
I tried to reason with you.

16:17.393 --> 16:20.353
-That was dishonest.
-You want to talk about honesty?

16:21.063 --> 16:22.730
Then you tell the truth.

16:23.232 --> 16:26.317
-Why don't you want him to have a dog?
-l already told you.

16:27.444 --> 16:31.030
He's a little boy,
and a dog is a big responsibility.

16:31.240 --> 16:36.244
No. He's not a baby. He's a
responsible boy who needs a friend.

16:37.830 --> 16:40.623
And what happens when
he becomes attached to that dog?

16:40.874 --> 16:42.417
Learns to love it?

16:42.876 --> 16:45.336
I thought that was the general idea.

16:45.546 --> 16:46.587
Ellen.

16:46.755 --> 16:48.965
Dogs die. They get sick.

16:49.216 --> 16:53.469
They run away, get hit by cars.
They're a heartbreak waiting to happen.

16:54.221 --> 16:56.097
He's not ready for that.

16:56.265 --> 17:00.768
He's frail, he's sensitive
and he can't handle it.

17:01.603 --> 17:04.771
How do you know what he can handle?

17:05.065 --> 17:06.482
You don't give him a chance.

17:06.775 --> 17:08.443
I know all about loss.

17:08.652 --> 17:10.903
Experienced more than my fair share.

17:11.113 --> 17:15.116
It's hard enough on an adult.
A boy shouldn't have to.

17:16.285 --> 17:19.287
So you're gonna
shelter him from life?

17:20.622 --> 17:22.290
For how long?

17:25.252 --> 17:27.127
He keeps the dog.

17:27.463 --> 17:28.671
For two weeks.

17:28.922 --> 17:31.674
If there's a problem,
I'll take it to the farm myself.

17:31.925 --> 17:33.009
Jack...

17:33.260 --> 17:36.012
...Will deserves this chance.
He needs it.

17:37.014 --> 17:38.181
Okay?

17:40.017 --> 17:41.309
Wait, l....

17:41.518 --> 17:44.896
-l haven't agreed to that.
-l'm not asking.

18:01.914 --> 18:06.167
[PUPPY WHlNES]

18:10.547 --> 18:12.006
Hey, boy!

18:12.508 --> 18:14.217
What's the matter?

18:14.843 --> 18:16.969
You miss your mommy and daddy?

18:17.179 --> 18:19.180
Your brothers and sisters?

18:24.478 --> 18:26.062
I'll take care of you.

18:26.688 --> 18:28.231
Don't be scared.

18:29.233 --> 18:30.858
I've got you.

18:33.362 --> 18:35.196
I'm an only child...

18:35.697 --> 18:37.698
...and now you're an only dog.

18:38.367 --> 18:41.369
WlLLIE:
I met him on the day I turned 9.

18:41.870 --> 18:45.081
He was just a trembling ball of fur.

18:45.666 --> 18:48.376
Scared and shy as I was.

18:50.587 --> 18:54.215
That night, lying in bed
before sleep...

18:54.383 --> 18:57.385
...I felt the beating of his heart
against my body.

18:58.053 --> 19:02.473
And though l didn't know it then,
he was to change my life forever.

19:02.724 --> 19:04.392
My dog, Skip.

19:04.601 --> 19:07.562
My best and most steadfast friend.

19:09.022 --> 19:12.275
[PUPPY WHlNlNG]

19:14.528 --> 19:17.864
[TEETH BRUSHlNG NOISES]

19:23.579 --> 19:27.081
Skip and l instantly
became the best of friends.

19:27.583 --> 19:30.585
He didn't mind that
I was scrawny and shy...

19:30.794 --> 19:34.088
...or that l liked books
a whole lot more than football.

19:35.132 --> 19:38.426
It was unconditional love
on both our parts.

19:40.262 --> 19:42.597
You've grown almost 2 inches.

19:43.265 --> 19:45.266
[GRUNTlNG]

19:47.311 --> 19:51.230
You could talk to him as well as
you could talk to many human beings.

19:51.440 --> 19:54.108
And much better than
you could talk to some.

19:54.443 --> 19:57.612
He'd sit down, look you
straight in the eye...

19:57.779 --> 20:01.824
...and when he understood you,
he'd turn his head sideways.

20:02.451 --> 20:06.245
I watched Skip grow from the puppy
who came to me from a farm...

20:06.455 --> 20:10.291
...into a sleek and dexterous,
affectionate dog.

20:10.542 --> 20:13.544
Skip became a true member
of the family.

20:20.135 --> 20:22.803
We played games together,
did household chores.

20:23.180 --> 20:24.805
That's my boy.

20:25.349 --> 20:27.058
[WHlNES]

20:27.809 --> 20:29.268
[SKlP GROWLING]

20:29.478 --> 20:32.146
Even my father had to admit...

20:32.481 --> 20:35.149
...Skip was an exceptional dog.

20:38.946 --> 20:41.572
[GROWLlNG]

20:42.616 --> 20:44.408
[LAPPING WATER]

20:44.576 --> 20:45.618
[SCHOOL BELL RlNGlNG]

21:16.984 --> 21:18.484
[CAR HORN HONKS]

21:18.694 --> 21:20.987
[CAR IGNlTION STARTING]

21:24.908 --> 21:25.950
What?

21:29.705 --> 21:30.705
[HONKING]

21:30.872 --> 21:33.624
MAN: Look at that, Margaret!
WOMAN: Take a look at that!

22:02.738 --> 22:04.572
Honk the horn, Skip!

22:24.718 --> 22:25.760
Yes, sir.

22:25.969 --> 22:27.011
[BARKS]

22:27.179 --> 22:29.430
Or should I say, "yes, sirs"?

22:29.890 --> 22:32.767
Pound of sausage, please.
I have our coupons.

22:32.976 --> 22:36.228
Think your friend there
might like a piece of bologna?

22:36.438 --> 22:39.774
I never met a dog that didn't
appreciate a good piece of bologna.

22:46.448 --> 22:48.824
Nobody has to know about that but us.

23:01.129 --> 23:05.091
[SKlP BARKS AND GROWLS]

23:09.513 --> 23:12.515
-Did you have those chops?
-Yes, ma'am. Coming right up.

23:18.730 --> 23:20.147
Is this your dog?

23:20.941 --> 23:21.982
Yeah.

23:22.150 --> 23:23.359
Skipper.

23:23.819 --> 23:25.361
Skip, for short.

23:25.612 --> 23:27.988
[BARKS]

23:28.240 --> 23:29.657
He's sweet.

23:35.997 --> 23:37.248
Rivers, let's go.

23:38.291 --> 23:39.500
Yes, ma'am.

23:41.503 --> 23:43.129
See you at school.

23:43.839 --> 23:45.339
Yeah. See you.

23:55.517 --> 23:57.852
Looks like he done did you a favor.

24:20.876 --> 24:22.877
Skip, l can't see a thing.

24:23.587 --> 24:24.628
KlD 1 :
Shh!

24:24.796 --> 24:25.838
I'm sorry.

24:26.047 --> 24:28.215
-Skip, where are you, boy?
KlD 2: Find a seat!

24:28.383 --> 24:30.217
Hey, cutie!

24:31.553 --> 24:34.054
-Come on down, boy.
KlD 3: Sit down!

24:34.723 --> 24:36.849
-Down!
KlD 3: Will you sit down, please?

24:38.602 --> 24:41.729
KlD 4: Why don't you sit down?
Your dog's sitting.

24:43.732 --> 24:45.399
I'm really sorry.

24:46.860 --> 24:49.361
I usually just let him
choose the seats.

24:50.071 --> 24:51.739
I seen.

24:55.619 --> 24:57.328
[BOYS LAUGHING]

25:10.467 --> 25:12.426
He's sitting by Rivers Applewhite.

25:13.094 --> 25:14.595
I can't believe it!

25:15.430 --> 25:18.224
The world ain't fair, I'm telling you.

25:18.433 --> 25:21.769
I guess girls must really go for dogs.

25:22.812 --> 25:24.063
ROOSEVELT [OVER RADlO]:
Freedom...

25:24.231 --> 25:28.442
...means the supremacy
of human rights everywhere.

25:30.278 --> 25:32.947
How long does it take mail
to get to Europe?

25:33.448 --> 25:34.782
Where in Europe?

25:35.283 --> 25:38.953
Where Dink is.
Foxhole in the south of France.

25:39.287 --> 25:40.412
[SKlP BARKS]

25:40.956 --> 25:42.498
Are you for Roosevelt, boy?

25:44.459 --> 25:47.127
What do you think about Hitler?

25:53.802 --> 25:55.010
[BARKS]

26:08.984 --> 26:10.693
Mrs. Jenkins, it's us.

26:10.944 --> 26:13.529
Come on in, fellas.
Be right with you.

26:14.197 --> 26:16.198
Another letter already?

26:30.672 --> 26:32.506
[BARKS]

27:08.043 --> 27:09.877
You know how to throw a curve?

27:10.754 --> 27:12.671
Dink's gonna show me
when he gets home.

27:12.881 --> 27:14.089
Who's Dink?

27:14.591 --> 27:16.258
Where are you from? Mars?

27:16.551 --> 27:18.761
Nope. Right across town over there.

27:19.012 --> 27:22.222
And you haven't heard of Dink Jenkins?

27:22.390 --> 27:26.060
He's only the best ballplayer
anywhere around here. Ever.

27:26.269 --> 27:28.979
Well, you haven't seen Waldo Grace.

27:29.397 --> 27:30.773
He a colored boy?

27:31.066 --> 27:33.692
Yep, and the best in the whole world.

27:34.736 --> 27:36.570
Besides Dink.

27:43.286 --> 27:44.912
He likes you.

27:47.582 --> 27:49.291
GRANDMA:
Hey, Willie!

27:49.584 --> 27:51.293
You got mail!

27:56.508 --> 27:57.591
POSTMAN:
From overseas.

27:58.426 --> 27:59.718
Look at this.

27:59.928 --> 28:01.261
Oh, boy!

28:03.098 --> 28:04.139
Wow.

28:19.114 --> 28:22.658
"And he said to his sons,
'Saddle the ass for me.'

28:22.909 --> 28:26.120
So they saddled the ass for him
and mounted it."

28:28.665 --> 28:30.332
[CLASS GASPS]

28:36.172 --> 28:39.758
[CLASS CLAMMERS]

28:39.968 --> 28:42.469
[CLASS LAUGHS]

28:51.855 --> 28:56.316
This right here is a musket
used in the Civil War.

29:05.160 --> 29:06.160
Now, then...

29:06.327 --> 29:08.495
...we have time for just one more.

29:08.788 --> 29:12.374
-Who would like to be next?
-l have a show-and-tell.

29:14.627 --> 29:18.464
This right here is
a German army helmet.

29:18.673 --> 29:22.092
Inside it says, "Hans."

29:23.470 --> 29:25.304
It's a dead Kraut's helmet.

29:25.513 --> 29:28.223
That ain't no real Kraut helmet.

29:29.601 --> 29:33.520
This is an ammo belt
with some writing. It says:

29:33.730 --> 29:37.733
"Gott mit uns," which means,
"God with us" in German.

29:38.318 --> 29:39.818
They think God's on their side?

29:40.028 --> 29:42.696
That right there proves
the stuff's not real.

29:42.906 --> 29:44.990
And this is a letter...

29:45.867 --> 29:49.244
...from a real Gl fighting overseas.

29:49.704 --> 29:50.871
"Dear Willie:

29:51.873 --> 29:55.709
Boy, was I ever happy to get
your letter and news of home.

29:56.002 --> 29:58.170
I can't wait to meet Skip.

29:58.379 --> 30:00.756
He sounds like a world-class dog.

30:01.007 --> 30:03.175
I can't tell you exactly where I am...

30:03.384 --> 30:07.846
...but l can tell you they don't serve
French fries in France. Hint, hint.

30:08.056 --> 30:12.851
And that all Kraut is sauerkraut,
if you ask me. Ha-ha-ha.

30:14.687 --> 30:17.064
Keep those letters coming, Willie-boy.

30:17.232 --> 30:20.400
And don't let anybody go breaking
my records while l'm gone.

30:20.568 --> 30:22.653
We'll have these boys licked soon...

30:22.862 --> 30:25.531
...and l'll be home in time
for baseball season.

30:25.740 --> 30:29.243
Signed, your friend and neighbor...

30:29.577 --> 30:31.662
...Private First-Class...

30:34.082 --> 30:37.584
-...Dink Jenkins."
KlD: Dink Jenkins?

30:37.752 --> 30:39.419
[CLASS GASPS]

30:44.092 --> 30:45.133
[SCHOOL BELL RlNGS]

30:54.102 --> 30:56.478
I read my letter from Dink today.

30:58.606 --> 31:01.483
Where'd you really get
that stuff, you big sissy?

31:05.238 --> 31:06.280
[SKlP WHlNES]

31:06.489 --> 31:08.448
Give me that damn letter!

31:15.790 --> 31:17.624
Get up and fight!

31:21.754 --> 31:23.130
We playing ball or not?

31:27.135 --> 31:28.802
You want your stuff back?

31:31.222 --> 31:33.473
Then you gotta play ball.

31:37.312 --> 31:38.729
SPlT:
Twenty-four, hut!

31:39.230 --> 31:40.522
BlG BOY:
Go out with it.

31:43.234 --> 31:44.276
Touchdown!

31:44.444 --> 31:46.236
BlG BOY:
Get him! Stay with him!

31:47.363 --> 31:48.488
Yeah!

31:51.326 --> 31:53.994
Look! Look! Did you see that?
They scored.

31:54.162 --> 31:55.203
Hut!

31:57.290 --> 31:58.540
BlG BOY:
Get up!

31:58.833 --> 32:02.836
I don't care if you're hurt!
Take the ball. l don't care.

32:04.505 --> 32:07.174
I told you.
Stay up here with the ball!

32:07.842 --> 32:09.134
Run! Run!

32:09.344 --> 32:12.012
Run!

32:13.056 --> 32:14.097
Yeah!

32:14.265 --> 32:17.184
Might as well stay down there.
You're not doing any good.

32:17.393 --> 32:18.560
HENJlE:
Okay, it's our ball.

32:18.811 --> 32:20.020
WlLLIE:
Hut!

32:20.521 --> 32:21.855
BlG BOY:
Get the ball!

32:24.567 --> 32:26.360
SPlT:
You little baby.

32:29.197 --> 32:30.989
SPlT:
Fourteen, 23...

32:31.532 --> 32:33.367
...1 7. Set. Hut, hut.

32:33.534 --> 32:34.785
SPlT:
Hut.

32:36.037 --> 32:37.287
[GRUNT]

32:39.415 --> 32:41.667
RIVERS: Get the ball, Will!
Get the ball, Will!

32:41.876 --> 32:43.794
Run! Run!

32:44.504 --> 32:45.879
Run for touchdown!

32:46.547 --> 32:49.216
Run, Will, run! Run for touchdown!

32:50.885 --> 32:52.052
[SKlP BARKS]

33:01.562 --> 33:03.730
RIVERS:
Run! Run!

33:09.821 --> 33:12.072
We won, Skip!
We scored a touchdown!

33:13.241 --> 33:14.574
Dog pile!

33:18.913 --> 33:22.207
Not a bad run, Willie, for a sissy.

33:29.090 --> 33:30.424
SPlT:
You missed!

33:32.760 --> 33:34.094
SPlT:
Throw it higher.

33:35.054 --> 33:37.264
BlG BOY: If l throw any harder,
I'll break the window.

33:37.473 --> 33:38.598
SPlT:
I bet he's asleep.

33:38.766 --> 33:39.975
What is it, boy?

33:40.268 --> 33:43.562
SPlT: He sleeps with teddy bears.
BlG BOY: I hate teddy bears.

33:43.771 --> 33:46.648
SPlT: Or with his mom.
HENJlE: Still got his baby blanket.

33:47.608 --> 33:48.942
SPlT:
There he is.

33:52.280 --> 33:53.780
BlG BOY:
Nice pajamas.

33:54.365 --> 33:55.782
Come on down.

33:58.244 --> 33:59.619
I better not.

33:59.871 --> 34:02.664
Don't make me come up there
and get you, "Wilma."

34:02.957 --> 34:05.292
Little baby!

34:07.462 --> 34:08.503
Okay.

34:08.670 --> 34:10.297
I'll be right down.

34:10.797 --> 34:11.840
BlG BOY:
Hey!

34:12.007 --> 34:13.675
Bring that Kraut stuff.

34:13.926 --> 34:15.677
And the dog.

34:15.928 --> 34:20.306
And clean underwear,
if you scare easy.

34:33.654 --> 34:34.654
[LOUD CLATTERING]

34:44.831 --> 34:46.333
It's you, Skip.

34:47.126 --> 34:49.127
You scared me there, boy.

34:49.670 --> 34:51.338
Go on back to bed.

34:51.505 --> 34:52.630
Go on.

35:12.360 --> 35:13.860
Big Boy.

35:14.695 --> 35:16.071
Spit.

35:16.864 --> 35:18.323
Where y'all at?

35:21.869 --> 35:23.703
[MUFFLED NOISES]

35:24.205 --> 35:26.206
You want to be one of us?

35:27.875 --> 35:30.168
Maybe. I mean...

35:31.379 --> 35:32.546
...l guess.

35:33.256 --> 35:36.550
Then you gotta pass the test.

35:44.767 --> 35:46.226
Where are we going?

35:46.561 --> 35:48.478
BlG BOY: You know who's buried here,
don't you?

35:48.688 --> 35:50.230
HENJlE:
My uncle's buried here.

35:50.565 --> 35:52.232
BlG BOY:
No, stupid.

35:52.608 --> 35:53.984
The witch.

35:54.527 --> 35:56.111
The witch of Yazoo.

35:57.738 --> 36:00.073
That's just an old wives' tale.

36:00.575 --> 36:02.200
SPlT:
That's what you think, buster.

36:02.618 --> 36:05.537
She was a genuine witch.

36:05.746 --> 36:09.249
Everybody knows she used to lure men
to her house to kill them.

36:10.251 --> 36:12.586
Why, she even let her cats...

36:12.795 --> 36:16.756
...lick their bones
after she got done with them.

36:18.092 --> 36:21.928
That is, until she got killed herself.

36:24.098 --> 36:26.433
You sure you wanna be one of us?

36:29.103 --> 36:30.604
I guess.

36:43.784 --> 36:47.579
One night, a boy about our age...

36:47.788 --> 36:49.456
...looked through her window...

36:49.749 --> 36:53.752
...and what he saw
chilled him right to the bone.

36:53.961 --> 36:57.047
He saw her murder two men
with her bare hands.

36:57.423 --> 36:59.174
The boy ran and told the cops...

36:59.467 --> 37:03.553
...and they got up a posse and chased
that witch into Miller's swamp.

37:04.472 --> 37:08.975
Before they could catch her,
she got stuck in quicksand.

37:10.102 --> 37:12.938
And slowly, as she sank
in the quicksand...

37:13.147 --> 37:15.815
...she swore two things:

37:16.108 --> 37:17.275
First...

37:17.485 --> 37:21.279
...one day she'd rise up from the grave
and burn down the whole town!

37:21.656 --> 37:23.698
And the other thing she swore was...

37:23.950 --> 37:29.079
...she'd find that boy who ratted
on her and drag him down to hell!

37:29.288 --> 37:30.956
[GROUP SCREAMS]

37:31.499 --> 37:33.458
[THUNDER CLAPS]

37:38.589 --> 37:43.343
If you stay all night, we'll know
for sure that you're one of us.

37:43.511 --> 37:45.011
But if you don't...

37:45.179 --> 37:48.139
...Dink's Kraut stuff is ours.

37:49.183 --> 37:51.184
And if we do stay all night...

37:52.144 --> 37:54.521
...we get the football signed by Dink.

37:58.025 --> 38:00.026
You got yourself a deal.

38:01.821 --> 38:02.862
Here.

38:03.030 --> 38:04.698
You might need this.

38:04.865 --> 38:06.825
[OWL HOOTS]

38:08.244 --> 38:09.536
Come on, Skip.

38:16.043 --> 38:17.669
[WHlNES]

38:19.213 --> 38:21.381
I'll take the first watch, boy.

38:22.508 --> 38:24.050
You rest.

38:31.058 --> 38:32.934
I give him 20 minutes.

38:33.227 --> 38:34.561
If he stays...

38:34.895 --> 38:36.521
...he's a better man than me.

38:36.731 --> 38:38.231
And if she kills him...

38:38.441 --> 38:41.067
...l got dibs on that dog.

38:42.403 --> 38:45.155
A sunbeam

38:45.906 --> 38:50.744
Jesus wants me for a sunbeam

38:51.954 --> 38:54.581
A sunbeam

38:58.294 --> 39:01.921
l'll be a sunbeam for Him

39:20.983 --> 39:24.402
[OWLS HOOTING]

39:35.831 --> 39:38.291
[CACKLING]

39:39.418 --> 39:40.835
Oh, no!

39:41.087 --> 39:43.963
[CATS SCREECHlNG]

39:55.726 --> 39:58.603
MlLLARD: Junior, we did good this week.
JUNlOR: Just hurry up.

39:58.813 --> 40:01.815
JUNlOR: lf we get to lzzard County,
they'll pay twice as much.

40:01.982 --> 40:03.983
JUNlOR:
Those boys get real thirsty out there.

40:04.151 --> 40:05.652
MlLLARD:
Don't you know it!

40:05.861 --> 40:07.529
[GLASS CLATTERlNG]

40:12.993 --> 40:14.953
JUNlOR: What the hell you doing?
Put that back.

40:15.162 --> 40:19.165
MlLLARD: l want a bottle for myself.
JUNlOR: You're drinking up all the profits.

40:20.126 --> 40:21.835
WlLLIE:
Moonshiners!

40:22.753 --> 40:24.295
Skip, no!

40:24.505 --> 40:25.672
[SKlP BARKS]

40:25.965 --> 40:29.509
-Millard, shut that mutt up.
-Hey, doggy! Who's a nice doggy?

40:29.844 --> 40:31.010
I'm good with dogs.

40:31.345 --> 40:34.347
Shut him up, unless you want
to go back to the joint.

40:39.770 --> 40:41.062
Junior.

40:42.398 --> 40:44.691
[SKlP GROWLS AND BARKS]

40:44.900 --> 40:45.942
MlLLARD:
Junior!

40:47.027 --> 40:48.361
Junior!

40:48.571 --> 40:49.654
JUNlOR:
Goddamn it!

40:51.031 --> 40:52.782
I'll take care of this mutt!

40:52.992 --> 40:54.033
No!!

40:54.326 --> 40:55.368
Ow!

40:56.370 --> 40:58.872
-What was that?
-Let's get out of here, Skip!

40:59.039 --> 41:00.206
Run!

41:01.041 --> 41:02.375
Get that kid!

41:09.091 --> 41:10.592
Come on, Skip!

41:12.803 --> 41:16.389
MlLLARD:
It's no use, kid! I'm gonna find you!

41:23.522 --> 41:25.732
[PANTS]

41:30.571 --> 41:32.572
Let's get out of here, Skip.

41:36.535 --> 41:38.328
Where do you think you're going?

41:56.722 --> 41:58.640
Listen to me, you little worm.

41:59.225 --> 42:01.726
You tell anybody where
we're hiding this...

42:01.936 --> 42:04.771
...you'll wake up to find
a dead pooch on your porch.

42:05.439 --> 42:06.481
See...

42:06.774 --> 42:08.983
...l been needing me a new billfold.

42:10.611 --> 42:14.989
I think one made out of genuine
dog hide would be right slick.

42:15.407 --> 42:17.742
[MILLARD BARKS MOCKlNGLY]

42:17.952 --> 42:20.078
JUNlOR:
Now, you look like a smart kid.

42:20.454 --> 42:23.414
You move one little pinkie
before the sun comes up...

42:23.624 --> 42:26.793
...you better think hard
about life without that mutt.

42:27.002 --> 42:29.462
Everybody needs a friend.

42:30.005 --> 42:32.465
[MOCK BARKS]

42:35.177 --> 42:36.219
Come on.

42:37.638 --> 42:38.972
Think l scared him enough?

42:39.390 --> 42:41.307
MlLLARD:
I think he peed his pants.

42:41.475 --> 42:43.685
JUNlOR:
Gonna have to change those shorts.

42:51.819 --> 42:53.152
[GROWLS]

42:59.660 --> 43:00.660
Damn!

43:00.953 --> 43:03.037
SPlT:
He killed a whole six-pack!

43:03.289 --> 43:05.498
He slept right by her grave.

43:07.668 --> 43:09.168
SPlT:
Damn!

43:20.180 --> 43:22.515
[YELLING AND BARKING]

43:27.438 --> 43:29.647
Bam! Bam! Bam!

43:32.192 --> 43:34.736
WlLLIE:
Because of Skip, I was able to cross...

43:34.987 --> 43:37.488
...the threshold
from childhood to boyhood...

43:37.698 --> 43:39.574
...from being on the outside...

43:39.867 --> 43:42.535
...to finding myself smack-dab
in the middle.

43:43.203 --> 43:45.872
He helped open my eyes
to the wonders of life.

43:46.165 --> 43:49.542
And l got to know the delta
like the palm of my hand.

43:49.835 --> 43:54.547
Every bend in the road,
every slope, every field.

43:54.715 --> 43:58.551
lt became as familiar to me
as grass or sunlight.

44:03.557 --> 44:07.101
But Skip opened my eyes
to other things too.

44:08.020 --> 44:11.564
-Sorry we're late.
-That's okay. l was late too.

44:11.857 --> 44:13.066
Hey, Skip.

44:13.359 --> 44:14.692
He likes you.

44:14.902 --> 44:17.737
I like him too. A lot.

44:20.240 --> 44:21.407
Huck Finn.

44:21.575 --> 44:24.035
It's about a boy who has adventures.

44:25.245 --> 44:29.540
This is Caddie Woodlawn.
It's about a girl who has adventures.

44:31.919 --> 44:33.753
Not too many boys like reading.

44:35.255 --> 44:36.422
I do.

44:36.715 --> 44:39.008
I'm thinking of becoming a writer.

44:39.259 --> 44:41.761
Either that or a U.S. senator.
One of those.

44:42.012 --> 44:44.263
I'll probably be a writer too.

44:44.431 --> 44:45.932
Or a pilot.

44:47.142 --> 44:51.104
Or maybe even a senator's wife.
Something like that.

44:52.523 --> 44:55.316
Well, l haven't really decided yet.

44:56.568 --> 44:57.819
Yeah.

44:58.112 --> 44:59.529
Me neither.

45:23.303 --> 45:24.470
MAN 1 :
Hey, Skip!

45:24.722 --> 45:25.763
MAN 2:
Hello there, Skip.

45:30.978 --> 45:33.479
WlLLIE:
Skip grew to know Yazoo too.

45:33.689 --> 45:36.983
It was a good place to grow up
for dogs as well as boys.

45:39.153 --> 45:43.990
Being friendly, he occasionally
wandered around town by himself...

45:44.158 --> 45:47.452
...and anyone of any consequence
knew who he was.

45:51.665 --> 45:53.499
GIRLS:
Hi, Skip.

45:54.835 --> 45:56.461
Hey, Skip.

46:06.180 --> 46:09.599
WlLLIE: One of Skip's favorite spots
was my dear old Aunt Maggie's.

46:09.808 --> 46:13.644
Her bridge games meant
finger sandwiches for the taking.

46:14.229 --> 46:16.898
And the strange creature
that was her pet...

46:17.191 --> 46:19.984
...was an endless source
of one-sided conversation.

46:20.194 --> 46:24.614
Lordy, Lordy! Lord have mercy!

46:25.824 --> 46:26.866
Y'all come back!

46:37.878 --> 46:40.671
WlLLIE:
Like all dogs, Skip was colorblind.

46:40.881 --> 46:44.842
He made friends easily with
people of all races and origins.

46:45.052 --> 46:47.261
The town was segregated back then...

46:47.513 --> 46:51.766
...but as we know, dogs are
a whole lot smarter than people.

47:10.577 --> 47:12.662
That's Waldo Grace.

47:23.090 --> 47:25.091
WALDO'S FRlEND:
Nice and easy. That's it.

47:29.096 --> 47:30.930
Skip!

47:39.606 --> 47:41.232
That's my Skip.

47:41.775 --> 47:42.775
Come on, boy.

47:42.943 --> 47:44.193
Bye.

47:47.906 --> 47:49.073
[CAR HORN HONKS]

47:59.501 --> 48:03.087
-Any of y'all heard of Waldo Grace?
BlG BOY: Who?

48:03.297 --> 48:06.132
Waldo Grace. Colored boy.

48:06.758 --> 48:08.217
They say he's better than Dink.

48:08.844 --> 48:09.886
You shut up.

48:11.138 --> 48:13.139
They say he's good at every sport.

48:13.640 --> 48:14.724
Let me tell you.

48:15.309 --> 48:18.144
Nobody around here
can beat Dink at nothing.

48:18.312 --> 48:19.854
Especially no colored boy.

48:20.230 --> 48:22.315
I'd like to see how good he is.

48:30.949 --> 48:35.244
Who's that man with the black mask?
He doesn't belong to the special army.

48:49.551 --> 48:51.177
After him, men!

48:51.386 --> 48:53.679
[AUDIENCE LAUGHS]

49:02.981 --> 49:06.025
NARRATOR:
Uncle Sam is looking for a few good...

49:06.193 --> 49:07.234
...dogs!

49:07.527 --> 49:08.569
That's right.

49:08.820 --> 49:12.531
Some of America's bravest soldiers
salute by wagging their tails.

49:13.283 --> 49:15.493
Yankee Doodle doggies from all over...

49:15.702 --> 49:18.162
...have dedicated their lives
to winning the war.

49:18.372 --> 49:20.873
Members of the Army's
crack K-9 Corps...

49:21.041 --> 49:25.169
...undergo a training as rigorous
as that of our fighting men.

49:25.379 --> 49:26.712
[GROWLS]

49:27.214 --> 49:28.339
[BARKS]

49:29.549 --> 49:30.716
NARRATOR:
Take that, Adolf!

49:30.884 --> 49:34.178
We're not pulling your leg.
We mean business!

49:35.847 --> 49:39.225
But not all of our four-legged
Gls make it home.

49:42.062 --> 49:44.230
Even the youngsters do their part.

49:44.398 --> 49:48.359
Para-pups, they're called,
and they aid our boys in the air.

49:53.448 --> 49:56.075
Who says dogs can't fly?

50:01.415 --> 50:05.209
Safe and sound on the ground.
Another successful mission.

50:05.419 --> 50:09.088
After a hard day's work,
these puppies need some R and R.

50:10.257 --> 50:12.758
Front and center, Fido.
Enlist today!

50:22.853 --> 50:26.397
KlDS:
Hup 2, 3, 4! Hup 2, 3, 4!

50:26.606 --> 50:29.400
We'll bomb them, and then
come down here to Libya...

50:29.609 --> 50:32.945
...and bomb the rest of the guys.
You got it? Okay.

50:38.660 --> 50:40.119
Go! Go! Go!

50:43.165 --> 50:44.874
Way to go, Skip!

50:45.083 --> 50:47.293
Those are the bad guys.
The Germans.

50:47.502 --> 50:50.629
Hitler! You want to kill Hitler!

51:03.977 --> 51:05.686
[BARKS]

51:15.489 --> 51:17.990
KlDS:
Get him, get him, get him!

51:18.700 --> 51:20.159
He's ready.

51:28.668 --> 51:31.670
That's about 1 6 inches high.
That's tall for a terrier.

51:32.005 --> 51:33.506
He's a real good eater, sir.

51:33.715 --> 51:34.965
I'm sure.

51:39.221 --> 51:40.513
I see.

51:41.181 --> 51:42.181
What?

51:42.349 --> 51:43.516
Mr. Morris...

51:43.683 --> 51:47.853
...this is as fine an animal as
